l n="shak. luc 450" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 450</bibl></cit>. <emph>our d. marches</emph> (changed) <cit><quote>to delightful measures,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 8</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this to me in d. secrecy impart they did,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.207" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 207</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>silence that d. bell,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.175" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 175</bibl></cit> (rung in fear and spreading fear).
